## Description {#details}

Iterator for intrusive lists based on <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-node">ilist&#95;node</a>.

Much like <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-iterator">ilist&#95;iterator</a>, but with the addition of two bits recording whether this position (when in a range) is half or fully open.

Definition at line 214 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/ilist-iterator-h">ilist&#95;iterator.h</a>.

### ilist&#95;iterator&#95;w&#95;bits() {#a708c3fab733a5f094aeebbd9be81f262}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class OptionsT, bool IsReverse, bool IsConst&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>llvm::ilist&#95;iterator&#95;w&#95;bits&lt; OptionsT, IsReverse, IsConst &gt;::ilist&#95;iterator&#95;w&#95;bits (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-iterator-w-bits">ilist&#95;iterator&#95;w&#95;bits</a>&lt; OptionsT, !IsReverse, IsConst &gt; &amp; RHS)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "explicit"]}>
Explicit conversion between forward/reverse iterators.

Translate between forward and reverse iterators without changing range boundaries. The resulting iterator will dereference (and have a handle) to the previous node, which is somewhat unexpected; but converting the two endpoints in a range will give the same range in reverse.

This matches std::reverse&#95;iterator conversions.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/ilist-iterator-h/#l00291">291</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/ilist-iterator-h">ilist&#95;iterator.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
